from sklearn.metrics import (
    accuracy_score, roc_auc_score, confusion_matrix, classification_report
)
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.naive_bayes import GaussianNB
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.svm import SVC
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
from xgboost import XGBClassifier
import warnings

warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

file_path = '/content/ARDS-Final_Python_code.csv'
data = pd.read_csv(file_path)

features = [
    'age', 'bmi_mean_imputed', 'bilirubin_avg', 'lactate_avg', 'glucose_avg',
    'potassium_avg', 'creatinine_avg', 'urine_avg', 'albumin_avg', 'bun_avg',
    'pCO2_avg', 'pt_avg', 'ptt_avg', 'valvular_disease', 'metastatic_cancer'
]
target = 'Target_variable_encoded'

X = data[features]
y = data[target]

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    X, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=42, stratify=y
)

models = {
    'Logistic Regression': LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=42),
    'Random Forest': RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=42),
    'XGBoost': XGBClassifier(use_label_encoder=False, eval_metric='logloss', random_state=42),
    'Naive Bayes': GaussianNB(),
    'K-Nearest Neighbors': KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=5),
    'Support Vector Machine': SVC(probability=True, random_state=42),
    'Decision Tree': DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=42)
}

results = []
for model_name, model in models.items():
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)

    y_train_pred = model.predict(X_train)
    y_train_proba = model.predict_proba(X_train)[:, 1] if hasattr(model, "predict_proba") else None

    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_train, y_train_pred)
    auc = roc_auc_score(y_train, y_train_proba) if y_train_proba is not None else "N/A"
    confusion = confusion_matrix(y_train, y_train_pred)
    classification = classification_report(y_train, y_train_pred)

    results.append({
        'Model': model_name,
        'Train Accuracy': accuracy,
        'Train AUC': auc,
        'Confusion Matrix': confusion.tolist(),
        'Classification Report': classification
    })

results_df = pd.DataFrame(results)
for idx, row in results_df.iterrows():
    print(f"\nModel: {row['Model']}")
    print(f"Train Accuracy: {row['Train Accuracy']}")
    print(f"Train AUC: {row['Train AUC']}")
    print("Confusion Matrix:")
    print(row['Confusion Matrix'])
    print("Classification Report:")
    print(row['Classification Report'])

results_df.drop(columns=['Confusion Matrix', 'Classification Report']).to_csv(
    'model_training_metrics.csv', index=False
)

Model Evaluation:

Performance metrics included AUC (Area Under the Curve), accuracy, sensitivity, specificity, positive predictive value (PPV), and negative predictive value (NPV).

In[46]:
def calculate_metrics(y_true, y_pred):
    tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred).ravel()
    sensitivity = tp / (tp + fn)
    specificity = tn / (tn + fp)
    ppv = tp / (tp + fp)
    npv = tn / (tn + fn)
    return sensitivity, specificity, ppv, npv

results = []
for model_name, model in models.items():

    model.fit(X_train, y_train)

    y_train_pred = model.predict(X_train)
    y_train_proba = model.predict_proba(X_train)[:, 1] if hasattr(model, "predict_proba") else None

    y_test_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    y_test_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1] if hasattr(model, "predict_proba") else None

    train_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_train, y_train_pred)
    train_auc = roc_auc_score(y_train, y_train_proba) if y_train_proba is not None else "N/A"
    train_sensitivity, train_specificity, train_ppv, train_npv = calculate_metrics(y_train, y_train_pred)

    test_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_test_pred)
    test_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_test_proba) if y_test_proba is not None else "N/A"
    test_sensitivity, test_specificity, test_ppv, test_npv = calculate_metrics(y_test, y_test_pred)

    results.append({
        'Model': model_name,
        'Train Accuracy': train_accuracy,
        'Test Accuracy': test_accuracy,
        'Train AUC': train_auc,
        'Test AUC': test_auc,
        'Train Sensitivity': train_sensitivity,
        'Test Sensitivity': test_sensitivity,
        'Train Specificity': train_specificity,
        'Test Specificity': test_specificity,
        'Train PPV': train_ppv,
        'Test PPV': test_ppv,
        'Train NPV': train_npv,
        'Test NPV': test_npv
    })

results_df = pd.DataFrame(results)

results_file = 'train_test_evaluation_metrics.csv'
results_df.to_csv(results_file, index=False)
print(f"Results saved to {results_file}")

print("Train and Test Evaluation Metrics:")
print(results_df)

In[47]:
from sklearn.feature_selection import mutual_info_classif

def plot_importance(importance_df, model_name):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='Importance', y='Feature', data=importance_df, palette='viridis')
    plt.title(f'Feature Importance - {model_name}')
    plt.xlabel('Importance')
    plt.ylabel('Feature')
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

# 1. Random Forest
rf_model = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)
rf_model.fit(X_train, y_train)
rf_importances = rf_model.feature_importances_
rf_importance_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'Feature': features,
    'Importance': rf_importances
}).sort_values(by='Importance', ascending=False)
plot_importance(rf_importance_df, 'Random Forest')

# 2. XGBoost
xgb_model = XGBClassifier(use_label_encoder=False, eval_metric='logloss', random_state=42)
xgb_model.fit(X_train, y_train)
xgb_importances = xgb_model.feature_importances_
xgb_importance_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'Feature': features,
    'Importance': xgb_importances
}).sort_values(by='Importance', ascending=False)
plot_importance(xgb_importance_df, 'XGBoost')

# 3. Logistic Regression
logreg_model = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=42)
logreg_model.fit(X_train, y_train)
logreg_coefficients = logreg_model.coef_[0]
logreg_importance_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'Feature': features,
    'Importance': np.abs(logreg_coefficients)
}).sort_values(by='Importance', ascending=False)
plot_importance(logreg_importance_df, 'Logistic Regression')

# 4. Naive Bayes (GaussianNB)
nb_model = GaussianNB()
nb_model.fit(X_train, y_train)
nb_importances = mutual_info_classif(X_train, y_train, random_state=42)
nb_importance_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'Feature': features,
    'Importance': nb_importances
}).sort_values(by='Importance', ascending=False)
plot_importance(nb_importance_df, 'Naive Bayes')

# 5. K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)
knn_model = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=5)
knn_model.fit(X_train, y_train)
knn_importances = mutual_info_classif(X_train, y_train, random_state=42)
knn_importance_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'Feature': features,
    'Importance': knn_importances
}).sort_values(by='Importance', ascending=False)
plot_importance(knn_importance_df, 'K-Nearest Neighbors')

    'Feature': features,
    'Importance': dt_importances
}).sort_values(by='Importance', ascending=False)
plot_importance(dt_importance_df, 'Decision Tree')

Assessed model performance using metrics across both training and testing datasets. Conducted receiver operating characteristic (ROC) curve analysis for visual comparison.

from sklearn.metrics import (
    roc_auc_score, roc_curve, accuracy_score, confusion_matrix
)

roc_data = []
results = []
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

for model_name, model in models.items():

    model.fit(X_train, y_train)

    y_train_pred = model.predict(X_train)
    y_train_proba = model.predict_proba(X_train)[:, 1] if hasattr(model, "predict_proba") else None

    y_test_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    y_test_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1] if hasattr(model, "predict_proba") else None

    train_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_train, y_train_pred)
    test_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_test_pred)
    train_auc = roc_auc_score(y_train, y_train_proba) if y_train_proba is not None else "N/A"
    test_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_test_proba) if y_test_proba is not None else "N/A"

    if y_test_proba is not None:
        fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test, y_test_proba)
        roc_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_test_proba)
        roc_data.append((model_name, fpr, tpr, roc_auc))
        plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label=f'{model_name} (AUC = {roc_auc:.2f})')

    results.append({
        'Model': model_name,
        'Train Accuracy': train_accuracy,
        'Test Accuracy': test_accuracy,
        'Train AUC': train_auc,
        'Test AUC': test_auc
    })

plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--', label='Chance Level (AUC = 0.50)')
plt.title('ROC Curve Comparison')
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate (FPR)')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate (TPR)')
plt.legend(loc='lower right')
plt.grid(alpha=0.3)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

results_df = pd.DataFrame(results)

results_file = '/content/model_validation_metrics.csv'
results_df.to_csv(results_file, index=False)
print(f"Results saved to {results_file}")

print("Model Validation Metrics:")
print(results_df)

from sklearn.metrics import precision_recall_curve
import numpy as np

models = {
    'Logistic Regression': LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=42),
    'Random Forest': RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=42),
    'XGBoost': XGBClassifier(use_label_encoder=False, eval_metric='logloss', random_state=42),
    'Naive Bayes': GaussianNB(),
    'K-Nearest Neighbors': KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=5),
    'Decision Tree': DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=42)
}

recall_data = []

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

for model_name, model in models.items():
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)

    y_test_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1] if hasattr(model, "predict_proba") else None

    if y_test_proba is not None:
        precision, recall, thresholds = precision_recall_curve(y_test, y_test_proba)


        threshold = 0.5
        y_test_pred_custom = (y_test_proba >= threshold).astype(int)
        tp = np.sum((y_test_pred_custom == 1) & (y_test == 1))
        fp = np.sum((y_test_pred_custom == 1) & (y_test == 0))
        fn = np.sum((y_test_pred_custom == 0) & (y_test == 1))
        precision_custom = tp / (tp + fp) if (tp + fp) > 0 else 0
        recall_custom = tp / (tp + fn) if (tp + fn) > 0 else 0


        recall_data.append({
            'Model': model_name,
            'Custom Recall (0.5)': recall_custom,
            'Custom Precision (0.5)': precision_custom
        })
    else:
        print(f"{model_name} does not support probability predictions.")

recall_df = pd.DataFrame(recall_data)
print("\nRecall and Precision Summary:")
print(recall_df)

recall_file = '/content/recall_precision_metrics_with_graph.csv'
recall_df.to_csv(recall_file, index=False)
print(f"Recall and Precision data saved to {recall_file}")

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))

bar_width = 0.35
positions = np.arange(len(recall_df['Model']))

ax.bar(positions, recall_df['Custom Recall (0.5)'], bar_width, label='Custom Recall (0.5)', alpha=0.8, color='blue')
ax.bar(
    positions + bar_width,
    recall_df['Custom Precision (0.5)'],
    bar_width,
    label='Custom Precision (0.5)',
    alpha=0.8,
    color='green'
)

ax.set_title('Custom Recall and Precision at Threshold 0.5', fontsize=16)
ax.set_xlabel('Model', fontsize=14)
ax.set_ylabel('Values', fontsize=14)
ax.set_xticks(positions + bar_width / 2)
ax.set_xticklabels(recall_df['Model'], rotation=45, ha='right')
ax.set_ylim([0, 1])
ax.legend()
plt.grid(alpha=0.3)
plt.tight_layout()

plt.show()
